HEADWORD: Acetyl
<hw>Ac"e*tyl</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acetum</ets> vinegar + Gr. <?/ substance. See <er>-yl</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A complex, hypothetical radical, composed of two
parts of carbon to three of hydrogen and one of oxygen. Its hydroxide is
acetic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
